              "Absolutely. Here\u2019s a **decadent, high-flavor recipe** that honors your Wagyu and shrimp \u2014 made for your pleasure-loving palette. Think: rich surf & turf over pasta, with a white wine garlic cream sauce, kissed with herbs, butter, and heat.\n\n---\n\n## **Wagyu & Shrimp Over Herb Cream Linguine**\n*Serves 2\u20133, indulgently.*\n\n### **Ingredients**\n\n#### *Protein & Pasta*\n- Wagyu top sirloin (room temp)\n- 0.9 lb shrimp, peeled & deveined\n- 8 oz linguine or pappardelle\n\n#### *Produce*\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1 shallot, finely diced\n- 1 lemon (zest + juice)\n- 1 tbsp fresh thyme\n- 2 tbsp fresh parsley, chopped (garnish)\n- Optional: handful baby spinach or arugula (for color)\n\n#### *Dairy & Cheese*\n- 2 tbsp unsalted butter\n- \u00be cup heavy cream\n- \u00bc cup grated Parmesan or Grana Padano\n- Optional: 1 tbsp cream cheese (for velvet texture)\n\n#### *Liquids & Oils*\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- \u00bc cup dry white wine or splash of brandy\n\n#### *Spices*\n- Sea salt & cracked black pepper\n- \u00bd tsp smoked paprika (for shrimp)\n- Pinch of crushed red pepper (optional heat)\n- Garlic powder (light dust on steak)\n\n---\n\n### **Steps**\n\n#### **1. Prep & Season**\n- Let the Wagyu steak sit out to reach room temp. Season both sides generously with salt, pepper, garlic powder.\n- Toss shrimp in olive oil, paprika, salt, pepper, lemon zest. Set aside.\n\n#### **2. Boil Pasta**\n- Salt a large pot of water like the sea. Boil linguine until just shy of al dente. Reserve 1 cup pasta water. Drain.\n\n#### **3. Sear Wagyu**\n- Heat cast iron or heavy skillet over medium-high. Add olive oil.  \n- Sear Wagyu 2\u20133 min per side (depending on thickness).  \n- Baste with butter and thyme during last 30 seconds.  \n- Rest on cutting board, loosely tented. Slice after resting.\n\n#### **4. Cook Shrimp**\n- In same pan, add a splash of oil if needed. Saut\u00e9 shrimp 1\u20132 min per side until just opaque. Deglaze with white wine. Let reduce slightly. Remove shrimp.\n\n#### **5. Make Sauce**\n- Lower heat. Add butter, shallots, and garlic. Saut\u00e9 until translucent.\n- Stir in heavy cream and a splash of pasta water. Simmer gently.\n- Melt in Parmesan (and cream cheese if using). Add lemon juice to taste.\n- Toss in drained pasta. Stir to coat. Add spinach now if using.\n\n#### **6. Assemble**\n- Nest pasta on plates.\n- Top with sliced Wagyu and shrimp.\n- Garnish with parsley, cracked pepper, and a final cheese snow.\n\n---\n\n### **Pleasure Pairings**\n- **Wine:** buttery Chardonnay or dry ros\u00e9  \n- **Bread:** toasted sourdough rubbed with garlic & olive oil  \n- **Mood:** low lighting, silk robe, something vibey in the background (*Alina Baraz*, *Massive Attack*, *Trip\u2019s rhymes*)  \n\n---\n\nWant a sultry name for this dish or a ritualized \u201cfirst bite\u201d blessing to go with it?"
